There are several pizzerias sprawled throughout my Bath Beach neighborhood, but Pizza D'Amore is my go-to pizzeria whenever I'm in the mood for fast, great Italian food.  I've tried several items from this place including the fresh mozzarella pizza, spaghetti, pasta fagioli soup, eggplant parmesan, and meatball hero.  They are all delicious, hot, and freshly-made.  The service is fast and friendly.  The workers who are of Mexican descent have a great sense of humor and always put a smile on my face whenever I place my order with them.  The interior of this place was recently redone in an impressive brick and wood style unlike other pizzerias in the area that tend to appear cold and uninteresting.  You can tell that this place is a constant labor of love to Frank, the owner.  And in reading the other Google reviews of this place, seeing how the owner pro-actively responds to each and every customer comment tells me how much he wants every customer to have a great experience here.  Large black & white photos of the immediate neighborhood are prominently displayed on the walls of this pizzeria and pay homage how this area used to look like over 50 years ago.  The owner has two other Pizza D'Amore locations in other parts of Brooklyn.  While I've never visited them, I'm sure they're just as good as this one.
